text.tspan: Yaws is a debilitating infectious disease that affects the skin and bones. The disease can be effectively treated
with antibiotics. Reported case numbers are limited by surveillance capacity.
Data source: World Health Organization - Global Health Observatory (2024)
Note: Reported case numbers are limited by surveillance capacity. Yaws is also currently endemic in Liberia, East Timor and the
Philippines but due to lack of surveillance there are no reported cases.
